Google Colab
So if you dont want to install Anaconda3 and want to perform the data science project online then
you can use the Google Colab where all the Machine Learning and Datascience libraries are available.

Link : https://colab.research.google.com/?utm_source=scs-index

--> How to connect to google drive in google Colab
-->Python Code

  import google.colab from drive
  drive.mount('\content\drive')
  
 by using the code above you can connect to the google colab and import the dataset from the drive.
 
